    "Even proprietary models such as GPT-4o, Claude, and Gemini not only produce incorrect outputs, but also occasionally claim an inability to perceive the visual content entirely, as illustrated in Appendix F. Interestingly, despite claims that some carefully distilled smaller models outperform their larger counterparts on mainstream benchmarks (Liu et al., 2024c; Bai et al., 2023b), our analysis reveals that scaling laws still hold for robustness: within the same model architecture, larger models consistently demonstrate better stability across visual variations.",
    "For an in-depth understanding of these vulnerabilities, this subsection focuses on LLaVA model, which provides full access to its training data, code, and parameters.",
